{{Infobox language | name = Mansim | nativename = ''mor Moi'' | states = [[Papua (Indonesian province)|Papua]] | region = Eastern [[Bird's Head]] | speakers = 50? | date = 2010 | ref = <ref name="Hammarström2015">Hammarström (2015) Ethnologue 16/17/18th editions: a comprehensive review: online appendices</ref> | familycolor = Papuan | fam1 = [[West Papuan languages|West Papuan]] | fam2 = East Bird's Head | fam3 = [[Hatam–Mansim languages|Hatam–Mansim]] | iso3 = none | glotto = mans1260 | glottorefname = Mansim }}
'''Mansim''', also known as '''Borai''' or '''Moi Brai''', is a [[West Papuan languages|West Papuan]] language language of the eastern [[Bird's Head Peninsula]] closely related to [[Hattam language|Hattam]]. As of 2010 there are rumours of 50 elderly speakers.<ref name="Hammarström2015"/>
== Phonology == Mansim has five vowels: /a, e, i, o, u/, and 16 consonants.<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/50699329|title=Languages of the eastern Bird's Head|date=2002|publisher=Pacific linguistics, Research School of Pacific and Asian Studies, Australian National University|others=Reesink, Ger P., Australian National University. Research School of Pacific and Asian Studies.|isbn=0858834944|location=Canberra|oclc=50699329}}</ref> {| class="wikitable" style="text-align:center" |+Consonants ! colspan="2" | ![[Bilabial consonant|Bilabial]] ![[Alveolar consonant|Alveolar]] ![[Palatal consonant|Palatal]] ![[Velar consonant|Velar]] ![[Glottal consonant|Glottal]] |- ! rowspan="2" |[[Stop consonant|Stop]] !<small>voiceless</small> |p |t |(c) |k | |- ![[Voice (phonetics)|<small>voiced</small>]] |b |d |(ɟ) |g | |- ! colspan="2" |[[Fricative consonant|Fricative]] | |s | | |(h) |- ! colspan="2" |[[Nasal consonant|Nasal]] |m |n | |ŋ | |- ! colspan="2" |[[Semivowel]] | | |j |w | |- ! colspan="2" |[[Liquid consonant|Liquid]] | |r~l | | | |} The status of /c, ɟ, h/ is uncertain, due to the single instance in the supporting text.
Like other Papuan languages, Mansim lacks a distinction between /r/ and /l/.
=== Stress === Mansim could have a tonal difference between homophones, since the various instances of ''bar'' ('something,' 'carry,' 'not') and ''tan'' ('inside,' 'far,' 'afraid') could need the use of a different pitch, but this is not seen in the data, although it is restricted. Stress seems to be placed in an iambic pattern over the clause, with stress placed on the second syllable. This means that person prefixes and first syllables of polysyllabilic words, with the exception of full personal pronouns, are unstressed. Citation markers and possessive pronouns can be stressed, but major categories like nouns and verbs do not necessarily attract main stress.
== Grammar == The basic word order of Mansim is [[Subject–object–verb|SOV (subject-object-verb)]]. In the noun phrase, the possessive pronoun is after the nominal position.<ref name=":0" />
