* {{IPA|[ŋ]}} was an allophone of {{IPA|/n/}} before a velar consonant.
* The voiced fricatives {{IPA|[β]}}, {{IPA|[ð]}}, {{IPA|[ɣ]}}, {{IPA|[ɣʷ]}} and {{IPA|[z]}} were in [[complementary distribution]] with word-initial voiceless fricatives {{IPA|[ɸ]}}, {{IPA|[θ]}}, {{IPA|[x]}}, {{IPA|[xʷ]}} and {{IPA|[s]}}, and were thus originally simply [[allophones]] of each other. However, at some point in the Proto-Italic period, the allophony was somewhat disrupted by the loss of the voiceless allophones {{IPA|[xʷ]}} and {{IPA|[θ]}}, which merged with {{IPA|[ɸ]}}. Scholars disagree on whether to reconstruct Proto-Italic with the phonemes {{IPA|/xʷ ~ ɣʷ/}} and {{IPA|/θ ~ ð/}} still present (hence assuming that the merger with {{IPA|[ɸ]}} was a later areal change that spread across all extant dialects, possibly occurring simultaneous with or after the loss of the corresponding voiced fricatives), or to reconstruct Proto-Italic with the phonemes' voiceless allophones merged into {{IPA|/ɸ ~ β/}}, and their voiced allophones becoming independent phonemes {{IPA|/ð/}}, {{IPA|/ɣʷ/}}. Both of these sounds are relatively uncommon cross-linguistically, and eventually they were eliminated in all later languages, but differently in each.

