===Verbs===

'''Present Aspect<ref>{{cite web|last1=Rix|first1=Helmut|title=Towards a reconstruction of Proto-Italic|url=http://www.pies.ucla.edu/WeCIEC/Rix_H_2002.pdf|website=Program in Indo-European Studies|publisher=UCLA|accessdate=24 June 2017|ref=3}}</ref>'''

From Proto-Indo-European, the Proto-Italic present aspect changed in a couple of ways. Firstly, a new past indicative suffix of {{lang|itc-x-proto|*-β-}} was created. This likely occurred due to the elision of word-final {{PIE|*i}} within the Indo-European primary verb endings (E.g. PIE Present Indicative {{PIE|*h₁ésti}} > PIt {{lang|itc-x-proto|*est}}, but also PIE Past Indicative {{PIE|*h₁ést}}). Secondly, the desiderative suffix of {{PIE|*-s-/-so-}} became the future suffix in Proto-Italic. The subjunctive of this desiderative-future, with a suffix of both -s- and a lengthening of the following vowel, was used to represent a ''potentialis'' and ''irrealis'' mood. Finally, while the subjunctive and the optative of PIE were still in principle different moods, the moods became merged in Post-PIt developments (E.g. PIt subjunctive {{lang|itc-x-proto|*esed}} vs optative {{lang|itc-x-proto|*siēd}} which became Latin present subjunctive {{lang|la|sit}}).

The PIE dual person was also lost within PIt verbs just as it was in PIt nouns.

'''First Conjugation'''

This Conjugation pattern was derived from the PIE suffix {{PIE|*-eh₂-yé-ti}}, and formed primarily denominative verbs (I.e. deriving from a noun or an adjective).

