{{Infobox language family |name=Samoic |altname=Samoic–Outlier |region=[[Polynesia]]n islands |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3=[[Oceanic languages|Oceanic]] |fam4=[[Central Pacific languages|Central Pacific]] |fam5=[[Polynesian languages|Polynesian]] |child1=[[East Uvean–Niuafo'ou languages|East Uvean–Niuafo'ou]] |child2=[[Ellicean languages|Ellicean]] |child3=[[Futunic languages|Futunic]] |child4=[[Pukapuka language|Pukapuka]] |child5=[[Samoan language|Samoan]] |child6=[[Tokelauan language|Tokelauan]] |glotto=none }}
The '''Samoic–Outlier languages''', also known as '''Samoic''' languages, are a purported group of [[Polynesian languages]], encompassing the Polynesian languages of [[Samoa]], [[Tuvalu]], [[American Samoa]], [[Tokelau]], [[Wallis and Futuna]], and [[Polynesian outlier]] languages in [[New Caledonia]], the [[Solomon Islands]], [[Vanuatu]], [[Papua New Guinea]], and the [[Federated States of Micronesia]]. The name "Samoic-Outlier" recognizes [[Samoan language|Sāmoan]].
==Classification== According to ''Ethnologue'' 16, the Samoic languages are as follows:
*[[East Uvean–Niuafo'ou languages|East Uvean–Niuafo{{okina}}ou]] **[[Niuafo'ou language|Niuafo{{okina}}ou]] (in [[Tonga]]) **[[Fakauvea|{{okina}}Uvea]] (also called Wallisian or East Uvean, on [[Wallis Island|{{okina}}Uvea]] or Wallis island, [[Wallis and Futuna]]) *[[Pukapukan language|Pukapukan]] ([[Pukapuka]] in the [[Cook Islands]]) *[[Samoan language|Samoan]] ([[Samoa]] and [[American Samoa]]) *[[Tokelauan language|Tokelauan]] ([[Tokelau]]) *[[Niuatoputapu language|Niuatoputapu]] (on [[Niuatoputapu]] in [[Tonga]], extinct) *[[Ellicean languages|Ellicean]] **[[Tuvaluan language|Tuvaluan]] ([[Tuvalu]]) **[[Kapingamarangi language|Kapingamarangi]] ([[Kapingamarangi]] in the [[Federated States of Micronesia]]) **[[Nukuoro language|Nukuoro]] ([[Nukuoro]] in the [[Federated States of Micronesia]]) **[[Ontong Java language|Ontong Java]] ([[Ontong Java]] in the [[Solomon Islands]]) **[[Sikaiana language|Sikaiana]] ([[Sikaiana]] in the [[Solomon Islands]]) **[[Takuu|Takuu language]] ([[Takuu]] in the eastern islands of [[Papua New Guinea]]) **[[Nukumanu language|Nukumanu]] ([[Nukumanu]] in the eastern islands of [[Papua New Guinea]]) **[[Nuguria language|Nuguria]] ([[Nuguria]] in the eastern islands of [[Papua New Guinea]]) *[[Futunic languages|Futunic]] **[[Anuta language|Anuta]] ([[Anuta]] in the [[Solomon Islands]]) **[[Fakafutuna|Futuna]] (or East Futunan, on [[Futuna Island, Wallis and Futuna|Futuna]] in [[Wallis and Futuna]]) **[[Futuna-Aniwa language|Futuna-Aniwa]] (or West Futunan, on [[Futuna Island, Vanuatu|Futuna]] and [[Aniwa Island|Aniwa]] in [[Vanuatu]]) **[[Emae language|Emae]] ([[Emae]] in [[Vanuatu]]) **[[Rennellese language|Rennellese]] ([[Rennell Island|Rennell]] in the [[Solomon Islands]]) **[[Mele-Fila language|Mele-Fila]] ([[Mele (Vanuatu)|Mele]] in [[Vanuatu]]) **[[Pileni language|Pileni]] ([[Pileni]] in the [[Solomon Islands]]) **[[Tikopia language|Tikopia]] ([[Tikopia]] in the [[Solomon Islands]]) **[[Fagauvea|Uvean]] (or West Uvean, on [[Ouvéa]], [[New Caledonia]])
